It in the western part of Orange County, Florida, United States. The city was established by Henry Harrel in 1857. It was formerly called Beulah. It is part of the Orlando–Kissimmee–Sanford, Florida Metropolitan Statistical Area. In 2022, 48,523 people lived there. ==References== Category:Cities in Florida
